from dataclasses import dataclass

@dataclass
class Triple:
    subject: str
    predicate: str
    object: str

# EVOLVE-BLOCK-START

def predict(triples: list[Triple]) -> str:
    # Create a sentence using the first triple
    sentence = f"{triples[0].subject} is a {triples[0].object}."

    # Iterate over the remaining triples and add them to the sentence
    for triple in triples[1:]:
        if triple.predicate in ["cityServed", "elevationAboveTheSeaLevel", "location", "operatingOrganisation", "runwayLength", "runwayName", "country", "isPartOf", "1stRunwayLengthFeet", "1stRunwaySurfaceType", "3rdRunwayLengthFeet", "icaoLocationIdentifier", "locationIdentifier", "elevationAboveTheSeaLevelInFeet", "iataLocationIdentifier", "nativeName", "leaderParty", "capital", "language", "leader", "owner", "1stRunwayLengthMetre", "4thRunwaySurfaceType", "5thRunwayNumber", "largestCity", "4thRunwayLengthFeet", "1stRunwayNumber", "elevationAboveTheSeaLevelInMetres", "administrativeArrondissement", "mayor", "2ndRunwaySurfaceType", "3rdRunwaySurfaceType", "runwaySurfaceType", "officialLanguage", "city", "jurisdiction", "demonym", "aircraftHelicopter", "transportAircraft", "currency", "headquarter", "class", "division", "order", "regionServed", "leaderTitle", "hubAirport", "aircraftFighter", "attackAircraft", "battle", "5thRunwaySurfaceType", "countySeat", "chief", "foundedBy", "postalCode", "areaCode", "foundingYear", "ceremonialCounty"]:
            sentence += f" {triple.subject} is located in {triple.object}."
        else:
            sentence += f" {triple.subject} is {triple.object}."

    return sentence
